author: IGN
description: Step into the surreal real of Ayasa: Shadows of Silence in this launch trailer for the upcoming action-adventure game. Ayasa: Shadows of Silence is a dark tale of survival and conscience, blending platforming, puzzles, and haunting beauty. Journey through surreal lands where every choice shapes the fate of a world on the edge of ruin. Will you restore the light or embrace the darkness? Ayasa: Shadows of Silence will be available on PC via Steam on November 28, 2025.
title: Ayasa: Shadows of Silence - Official Launch Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the 'Screenvision' Featurette for Zootopia 2, an upcoming Walt Disney Animation Studios film starring Ginnifer Goodwin and Jason Bateman. Get a new look at a slice of life in the bayou with a specific greeting in Zootopia 2, in theaters on November 26, 2025.

After cracking the biggest case in Zootopia’s history, rookie cops Judy Hopps (voice of Ginnifer Goodwin) and Nick Wilde (voice of Jason Bateman) find their partnership isn’t as solid as they thought when Chief Bogo (voice of Idris Elba) orders them to join the Partners in Crisis counseling program. But it doesn’t take long for their partnership to be put to the ultimate test when they find themselves on the twisting trail of a mystery tied to the arrival of a venomous snake in the animal metropolis. The trailer, poster and trailer stills are now available to download and share.

title: Zootopia 2 - Official 'Screenvision' Featurette (2025) Ginnifer Goodwin, Jason Bateman, Ke Huy Quan

author: IGN
description:
Watch a Horus Heresy and Warhammer 40,000 expert react to your grimdark questions! How would you explain what the Horus Heresy is to someone who knows almost nothing about it, and how does it relate to Warhammer 40K? 

Well, we got Arbitor Ian, a Warhammer 40,000 master, to answer a collection of r/40kLore subreddit questions, from figuring out what the Xenos factions were doing during the Horus Heresy, to whether or not Horus was stronger than Emperor of Mankind, and a whole lot more! Arbitor Ian is a Warhammer content creator with a focus on introducing 40K lore to newcomers and veterans alike.

For more Warhammer 40,000 check out this history of Warhammer video games! https://youtu.be/EpIWUlG_5-0

📺 Watch Arbitor Ian's videos here: https://www.youtube.com/c/ArbitorIan
📸 View Arbitor Ian's Instagram page here: https://www.instagram.com/arbitorian

#IGN #Warhammer #ArbitorIan
title: Warhammer 40,000 Expert Answers Horus Heresy Questions

author: IGN
description:
The final season of Stranger Things kicks off with a four episode volume 1 just in time for Thanksgiving binge watching! As the citizens of Hawkins, Indiana prepare for a final showdown with Vecna and the upside down, the first episode drop from Stranger Things season 5 is off to a great start. 

Reviewer Tara Bennett and IGN's Clint Gage talk about the nearly half a billion dollar budget for this final season, balancing the "kids playing D&D in their basement" energy of the first season with a blockbuster Hollywood ending and how the Duffer Brothers seemed to be shaking off some rust after a long layoff after season 4.

Let us know what you thought of the Stranger Things Season 5 vol 1 and for everything else from the upside down, be sure to subscribe to IGN!
title: Stranger Things Season 5 Vol. 1 Review
